SO_REUSEADDR (&4)
#Parent SOL_SOCKET
#Wrap off
Meaning:	Changes the use of TIME_WAIT on disconnect
Value:		&4
#Wrap

Enables or disables the reuse of local addresses during the wait period that normally occurs when a TCP stream socket is closed. The argument is a single word which contains zero to disable this option, or a non-zero value to enable it.